text_response: Yes, this is true.  Wolf packs have an "alpha" wolf, which is the leader of the pack.  The alpha wolf is the oldest and most dominant wolf in the pack, and all the other wolves in the pack respect and obey the alpha wolf.  When the alpha wolf dies, another wolf will usually take over as the new alpha.  This new alpha wolf is usually younger than the previous alpha wolf, so the younger wolves overthrow the old alpha to become the new leader.
